---
import BaseLayout from '../../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';

const base = import.meta.env.BASE_URL;

const qualMethods = [
  {
    href: `${base}methods/qual/interviews/`,
    title: 'Interviews',
    desc: 'Semi-structured and in-depth interviews, plus rigour criteria.',
  },
  {
    href: `${base}methods/qual/focus-groups/`,
    title: 'Focus groups',
    desc: 'Group size, number of sessions, and shared-experience insights.',
  },
  {
    href: `${base}methods/qual/observation/`,
    title: 'Observation',
    desc: 'Behavior in natural settings, document analysis, and cultural context.',
  },
  {
    href: `${base}methods/qual/themes/`,
    title: 'Themes',
    desc: 'Content and narrative analysis, coding into themes and conceptual models.',
  },
  {
    href: `${base}methods/qual/projective-technique/`,
    title: 'Projective technique',
    desc: 'Indirect questioning — e.g. would you recommend X to someone else?',
  },
  {
    href: `${base}methods/qual/sentence-completion/`,
    title: 'Sentence completion',
    desc: 'Structured prompts — e.g. I love X because …',
  },
];
---

<BaseLayout title="Qual" description="Qualitative methods — interviews, focus groups, observation, and thematic analysis">
  <div class="qual-layout">
    <nav class="qual-toc" aria-label="On this page">
      <h2 class="qual-toc-title">On this page</h2>
      <ol class="qual-toc-list">
        <li><a href="#intro">Introduction</a></li>
        <li>
          <a href="#method">Method</a>
          <ol>
            {qualMethods.map((item) => (
              <li><a href={item.href}>{item.title}</a></li>
            ))}
          </ol>
        </li>
        <li><a href="#measurement">Measurement</a></li>
        <li><a href="#sampling">Sampling</a></li>
        <li><a href="#data-analysis">Data analysis</a></li>
      </ol>
    </nav>

    <article class="qual-article">
      <p class="back-link"><a href={`${base}methods/`}>← Methods</a></p>
      <h1 id="intro">Qual</h1>
      <p class="qual-lead">
        Non-numerical data (words): interviews, focus groups, observation, and document analysis to understand meaning
        and build themes. <strong>Data is always contextual. Not theory (content).</strong>
      </p>
      <p class="qual-lead">Qualitative data is to help understand, to give meaning.</p>

      <div class="qual-intro-block">
        <h2 class="qual-intro-heading">Defining qualitative research</h2>
        <ul class="qual-intro-list">
          <li>
            Qualitative research is an <strong>umbrella term</strong> for a family of approaches.
          </li>
          <li>
            It focuses on understanding <strong>participants&rsquo; points of view</strong>.
          </li>
          <li>
            Aims to generate rich insights (<strong>rather than confirming hypotheses</strong>) and develop theoretical
            contributions from empirical data.
          </li>
          <li>
            Concerned with <strong>diverse approaches</strong> shaped by distinct purposes and methodologies.
          </li>
          <li>
            Often applied when phenomena are new and <strong>theorizing is nascent</strong>.
          </li>
        </ul>
        <blockquote class="qual-quote">
          <p>
            &ldquo;Qualitative research is a situated activity that locates the observer in the world. It consists of a set
            of interpretive, material practices that make the world visible. These practices transform the world. They turn
            the world into a series of representations, including field notes, interviews, conversations, photographs,
            recordings, and memos to the self. At this level, qualitative research involves an interpretive, naturalistic
            approach to the world. This means that qualitative researchers study things in their{' '}
            <strong>natural settings</strong>, attempting to make sense of, or interpret, phenomena in terms of the
            meanings people bring to them.&rdquo;
          </p>
          <footer class="qual-quote-attribution">(Denzin &amp; Lincoln, 2005a, p. 3)</footer>
        </blockquote>
        <p class="qual-reference">
          Denzin, N.K. and Lincoln, Y.S. (2005) Introduction: The Discipline and Practice of Qualitative Research. In:
          Denzin, N.K. and Lincoln, Y.S., Eds., <em>Handbook of Qualitative Research</em>, 3rd Edition, Sage, Thousand
          Oaks, 1&ndash;32.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="qual-intro-block">
        <h2 class="qual-intro-heading">Research questions &amp; &ldquo;products&rdquo;</h2>
        <p class="qual-intro-prose">
          Qualitative research is useful for addressing two main types of questions:
        </p>
        <ul class="qual-intro-list">
          <li><strong>Descriptive</strong></li>
          <li><strong>Mechanistic</strong></li>
        </ul>
        <p class="qual-intro-prose">
          <strong>Descriptive questions</strong> ask: <strong>what</strong> is happening, for <strong>whom</strong>, and in{' '}
          <strong>what</strong> circumstances.
        </p>
        <p class="qual-intro-prose">
          <strong>Mechanistic questions</strong> ask: <strong>how</strong> a phenomenon of interest is happening.
        </p>
        <p class="qual-intro-prose"><strong>Products of qualitative research:</strong></p>
        <ul class="qual-intro-list">
          <li>Recurrent themes or hypotheses</li>
          <li>Survey instrument measures</li>
          <li>Taxonomies</li>
          <li>Conceptual models (or theories)</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="qual-reference">
          Agee, J. (2009). Developing qualitative research questions: A reflective process.{' '}
          <em>International Journal of Qualitative Studies in Education</em>, 22(4), 431&ndash;447.
        </p>
        <p class="qual-reference">
          Jennifer, M. A., &amp; Dolan, E. L. (2023). Venturing into qualitative research: A practical guide to getting
          started. <em>Scholarship and Practice of Undergraduate Research</em>, 7(1).
        </p>
      </div>

      <section id="method" class="qual-section">
        <h2>Method</h2>
        <p>Primary qualitative data collection techniques — open each for full detail.</p>
        <ul class="qual-method-nav">
          {qualMethods.map((item) => (
            <li>
              <a href={item.href} class="qual-method-nav-link">
                <span class="qual-method-nav-title">{item.title}</span>
                <span class="qual-method-nav-desc">{item.desc}</span>
              </a>
            </li>
          ))}
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section id="measurement" class="qual-section">
        <h2>Measurement</h2>
        <p>Interviewer manual</p>
      </section>

      <section id="sampling" class="qual-section">
        <h2>Sampling</h2>
        <p>Target population</p>
      </section>

      <section id="data-analysis" class="qual-section">
        <h2>Data analysis</h2>
        <p>Content and narrative analysis &mdash; coding into themes that can inform a conceptual model.</p>

        <h3 class="qual-subheading">Qualitative data</h3>
        <p>Work through the analysis in this order:</p>
        <ol class="qual-analysis-steps">
          <li><strong>Describe sample</strong> &mdash; describe the realised sample that took part in the study.</li>
          <li>
            <strong>Discuss themes</strong> &mdash; identify themes in the data, then discuss them using direct quotes from
            participants as the primary source of evidence.
          </li>
          <li><strong>Draw conclusion</strong> &mdash; draw conclusions from the sample description and thematic discussion.</li>
        </ol>
        <p>
          At the heart of the analysis: <strong>describe the realised sample</strong> and <strong>identify themes</strong>{' '}
          before you move on to interpretation and conclusions.
        </p>
      </section>
    </article>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>

<style is:global>
  html {
    scroll-behavior: smooth;
    scroll-padding-top: 6rem;
  }
</style>

<style>
  .back-link {
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    font-size: 0.9rem;
  }
  .back-link a {
    color: var(--color-maroon);
  }

  .qual-layout {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    gap: 2rem;
    align-items: start;
    max-width: 1100px;
  }

  @media (min-width: 900px) {
    .qual-layout {
      grid-template-columns: min(240px, 26%) 1fr;
    }
  }

  .qual-toc {
    position: sticky;
    top: 5.5rem;
    z-index: 1;
    padding: 1rem 1.1rem;
    background: #fff;
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    border-radius: 10px;
    border-left: 4px solid var(--color-maroon);
    font-size: 0.88rem;
    line-height: 1.45;
    max-height: calc(100vh - 6rem);
    overflow-y: auto;
  }

  .qual-toc-title {
    font-family: var(--font-sans);
    font-size: 0.72rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.04em;
    color: var(--color-ink-muted);
    margin: 0 0 0.65rem 0;
  }

  .qual-toc-list {
    margin: 0;
    padding: 0;
    list-style: none;
  }

  .qual-toc-list > li {
    margin-bottom: 0.45rem;
  }

  .qual-toc-list ol {
    margin: 0.35rem 0 0.5rem 0;
    padding-left: 1rem;
    list-style: none;
    border-left: 2px solid var(--color-border);
  }

  .qual-toc-list ol li {
    margin-bottom: 0.3rem;
  }

  .qual-toc a {
    color: var(--color-maroon);
    text-decoration: none;
  }

  .qual-toc a:hover {
    text-decoration: underline;
  }

  .qual-article {
    min-width: 0;
  }

  .qual-article h1 {
    font-family: var(--font-serif);
    font-size: clamp(1.45rem, 3vw, 1.85rem);
    color: var(--color-maroon);
    margin: 0 0 1rem 0;
    scroll-margin-top: 5.5rem;
  }

  .qual-lead {
    margin: 0 0 1rem 0;
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: var(--color-ink);
    max-width: 42rem;
  }

  .qual-intro-block {
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
    max-width: 42rem;
  }

  .qual-intro-heading {
    font-family: var(--font-serif);
    font-size: 1.2rem;
    color: var(--color-maroon);
    margin: 0 0 0.85rem 0;
  }

  .qual-intro-list {
    margin: 0 0 1.25rem 0;
    padding-left: 1.5rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: var(--color-ink);
  }

  .qual-intro-list li {
    margin-bottom: 0.55rem;
  }

  .qual-intro-prose {
    margin: 0 0 0.75rem 0;
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: var(--color-ink);
  }

  .qual-quote {
    margin: 0 0 1rem 0;
    padding: 0 0 0 1rem;
    border-left: 3px solid var(--color-maroon-muted);
  }

  .qual-quote p {
    margin: 0 0 0.65rem 0;
    line-height: 1.65;
    color: var(--color-ink);
    font-size: 0.95rem;
  }

  .qual-quote-attribution {
    font-size: 0.88rem;
    color: var(--color-ink-muted);
    font-style: italic;
  }

  .qual-reference {
    margin: 0;
    font-size: 0.82rem;
    line-height: 1.55;
    color: var(--color-ink-muted);
  }

  .qual-section {
    margin-top: 2.5rem;
    scroll-margin-top: 5.5rem;
  }

  .qual-section > h2 {
    font-family: var(--font-serif);
    font-size: 1.35rem;
    color: var(--color-maroon);
    margin: 0 0 1rem 0;
    line-height: 1.3;
    scroll-margin-top: 5.5rem;
  }

  .qual-subsection {
    margin-top: 1.75rem;
    scroll-margin-top: 5.5rem;
  }

  .qual-method-nav {
    margin: 0;
    padding: 0;
    list-style: none;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.65rem;
    max-width: 42rem;
  }

  .qual-method-nav-link {
    display: block;
    padding: 0.85rem 1rem;
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    border-radius: 8px;
    border-left: 3px solid var(--color-maroon);
    text-decoration: none;
    color: inherit;
    transition: border-color 0.2s, box-shadow 0.2s;
  }

  .qual-method-nav-link:hover {
    border-color: var(--color-maroon-muted);
    box-shadow: var(--shadow-md);
    text-decoration: none;
    color: inherit;
  }

  .qual-method-nav-title {
    display: block;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--color-maroon);
    margin-bottom: 0.2rem;
  }

  .qual-method-nav-desc {
    display: block;
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    line-height: 1.5;
    color: var(--color-ink-muted);
  }

  .qual-subheading {
    font-family: var(--font-serif);
    font-size: 1.05rem;
    color: var(--color-ink);
    margin: 1.25rem 0 0.75rem 0;
  }

  .qual-section p,
  .qual-subsection p {
    margin: 0 0 1rem 0;
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: var(--color-ink);
    max-width: 42rem;
  }

  .qual-analysis-steps {
    margin: 0 0 1rem 0;
    padding-left: 1.5rem;
    line-height: 1.75;
    max-width: 42rem;
  }

  .qual-analysis-steps li {
    margin-bottom: 0.65rem;
  }
</style>
